import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.Arrays;
import java.util.List;

public List<List<Integer>> minimumAbsDifference(int[] arr) {
    Arrays.sort(arr);
    int min_difference = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
    List<List<Integer>> result = new ArrayList<>();

    for (int i = 1; i < arr.length; ++i) {
        int difference = arr[i] - arr[i - 1];
        if (difference < min_difference) {
            min_difference = difference;
            result.clear();
            result.add(Arrays.asList(arr[i - 1], arr[i]));
        } else if (difference == min_difference) {
            result.add(Arrays.asList(arr[i - 1], arr[i]));
        }
    }

    return result;
}
```

    1. Sort the array in ascending order.
2. Initialize the minimum absolute difference variable `min_difference` and an empty result list.
3. Iterate through the sorted array from the second element to the last element, calculate the difference between the current element and the previous element.
4. If the difference is less than the current `min_difference`, update the `min_difference` variable and reset the result list with this new pair of elements.
5. If the difference is equal to the current `min_difference`, append this pair of elements to the result list.
6. Return the result list after processing all elements in the sorted array.
